NOAA National Centers for Environmental information, Climate at a Glance: Global Time Series, published June 2023, retrieved on June 19, 2023 from https://www.ncei.noaa.gov/access/monitoring/climate-at-a-glance/global/time-series

The 12 bullet points correspond to the 12 months. We have monthly data on temperature anomaly for the years 1850-2022. It would probably be more sensible to look at data at various latitudes for a fixed month.
